ITV.Tour.de.France.2014.Stage.11.Highlights.PDTV.x264-NX

Wednesday 16th July 2014 ITV4
7pm to 8pm Highlights

Highlights of of stage 11 with the riders back on the road after their first rest day with a 187km stage between Besancon and Oyonnax. This is an undulating route with four categorised climbs in the last 56km and a thrilling descent into Oyonnax to finish. If a breakaway does not succeed today, it could be the perfect stage for a rider like Peter Sagan. Presented by Gary Imlach with analysis from Chris Boardman, commentary by Phil Liggett and Paul Sherwen with Ned Boulting the reporter at the roadside.
